The paper deals with wireless sensor networks and estimation, which are topics that are commonly studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of phase shifts and wireless transmission also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the Signal Processing (cs.SY) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes algorithms for solving the estimation problem, which could also make it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
